ZCZC EE71
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 042300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A DPN LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER
NERN SCOTLAND. OVERNIGHT THE LOW IS FCST TO MOV SLWY E/SEWARDS INTO THE
N SEA AND LIE 965 OFF THE E COAST OF DENMARK BY MIDDAY THURSDAY. THE LOW
IS THEN FCST TO CONTINUE ITS EWARDS AND BEGIN TO FILL. ALSO ON FRIDAY A
SHALLOW LOW IS EXP TO MOV EWARDS ACROSS N FITZROY BISCAY AND CONTINENTAL
EUROPE. HIGH PRESSURE THEN BUILDS FM THE W BECMG CENTRED OVER BISCAY MIDDAY
SATURDAY AND EXTENDING A RIDGE NWARDS ACROSS THE UK. MEANWHILE A LARGE LOW
PRESSURE SYSTEM DEVELOPS TO THE W OF FITZROY. ON WEDNESDAY NIGHT STRG TO
NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO SPREAD E ACROSS NITON. WINDS GENERALLY EASING
FM THE NW FM MIDDAY THURSDAY BUT REMAINING STRG IN S FITZROY AND BISCAY
UNTIL FRIDAY AFTERNOON. ON SATURDAY GALE TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP
TO DEVELOP IN W FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON
NNNN